This paper discusses techniques for improving the performance and efficiency of branch predictors in modern processors, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories of computer science. The most likely category is cs.AR (Architecture), which deals with the design and optimization of computer systems. The paper also touches on cs.PF (Performance), which focuses on improving the speed and efficiency of computer systems, as well as cs.PL (Programming Languages), which deals with the design and implementation of programming languages and compilers. Additionally, the paper may be relevant to researchers in cs.ARCH (Computer Architecture) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), as these fields are closely related to processor design and optimization.
